Practical No: 3
A.	Fixers Utilities
â—	Removing leading & lagging spaces from a data entry
Code:
baddata = "     Data Science with too many spaces is bad!!!     "
print('>',baddata,'<')
cleandata=baddata.strip()
print('>',cleandata,'<')
Output: 

 


â—	Removing nonprintable characters from a data entry
Code:
import string
printable = set(string.printable)
baddata = "Data\x00Science with\x02 funny characters is \x10bad!!!"
cleandata=''.join(filter(lambda x: x in string.printable,
baddata))
print(cleandata)
Output:
 

â—	Reformatting data entry to match specific formatting criteria. Convert 2017/01/31 to 31 January 2017
Code:
import datetime as dt
baddate = dt.date(2017, 1, 31)
baddata=format(baddate,'%Y-%m-%d')
print(baddata)
gooddate = dt.datetime.strptime(baddata,'%Y-%m-%d')
gooddata=format(gooddate,'%d %B %Y')
print(gooddata)
